body:
Here is a minimal example:

```verilog
module t(/*AUTOARG*/
    // Inputs
    clk
);
    input clk;

    reg clk_en = 1'b0;
    wire clk_gated = clk & clk_en;
    wire [1:0] clks = {1'b0, clk_gated};

    always @(posedge clks[0])
        $display("ERROR: clks[0] should not be active!");
endmodule
```

In Verilator 4.032, this displays the error message at every tick of `clk`.

In the waveforms, I can see that clk_gated and clks[1:0] are correctly set to 0. However, the always block still triggers.

I had some limited success using `/* verilator var_split */` on `clks`. However, this does not work if I want to pass `clks` to a submodule.
